      "supporting_text": "Thus, we examined KGN-loaded nanoparticle suspension stability by DLS"
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s16",
      "source_region_type": "experimental_design",
      "source_locator_text": "EXPERIMENTAL_DESIGN_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "The diameter of all nanoparticle formulations generally increased to over 1 µ m over the 21-day release period"
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s17",
      "source_region_type": "experimental_design",
      "source_locator_text": "EXPERIMENTAL_DESIGN_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "PDI also increased during this time with PLGA particles exhibiting the largest PDI at the end of the 21-day release (~ 0.7)."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s18",
      "source_region_type": "experimental_design",
      "source_locator_text": "EXPERIMENTAL_DESIGN_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "However, PLGA–PEG nanoparticles showed a large increase in the hydrodynamic diameter (a maximum of 2–3 µ m) and PDI (a maximum ~ 0.5) at these conditions."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s19",
      "source_region_type": "experimental_design",
      "source_locator_text": "EXPERIMENTAL_DESIGN_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "Interestingly, despite maintaining a consistent hydrodynamic diameter over 7 days, PLGA–PEG–HA particles at 37 °C experienced an increase in PDI, also reaching a maximum of ~ 0.5 following 1 day of incubation."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s20",
      "source_region_type": "experimental_design",
      "source_locator_text": "EXPERIMENTAL_DESIGN_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "We examined hMSC viability in the presence of nanoparticles at concentrations above the equivalent KGN half maximal effective concentration (EC 50 ) of 100 nM."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s21",
      "source_region_type": "experimental_design",
      "source_locator_text": "EXPERIMENTAL_DESIGN_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "Next, we investigated nanoparticle interactions with hMSCs by loading FITC during nanoparticle fabrication."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s22",
      "source_region_type": "experimental_design",
      "source_locator_text": "EXPERIMENTAL_DESIGN_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "Figure 4 a shows the effect of incubation of FITC-loaded nanoparticles with hMSCs at an intermediate concentration (0.1 mg/mL) for varying time."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s23",
      "source_region_type": "experimental_design",
      "source_locator_text": "EXPERIMENTAL_DESIGN_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "KGN-Loaded Nanoparticle Mediated hMSC Chondrogenesis"
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s24",
      "source_region_type": "experimental_design",
      "source_locator_text": "EXPERIMENTAL_DESIGN_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "Nanoparticle concentrations were selected for each formulation by calculating the amount of nanoparticles necessary to ensure release 100 nM KGN over 3 days based on the in vitro release data."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s25",
      "source_region_type": "experimental_design",
      "source_locator_text": "EXPERIMENTAL_DESIGN_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "Total DNA (Fig. S6) and sGAG content per pellet wet weight (w/w) (Fig. 5 ) were quantified."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s26",
      "source_region_type": "experimental_design",
      "source_locator_text": "EXPERIMENTAL_DESIGN_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "by comparing KGN-loaded PLGA, PLGA–PEG, and PLGA–PEG–HA nanoparticles."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s27",
      "source_region_type": "experimental_design",
      "source_locator_text": "EXPERIMENTAL_DESIGN_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "Here, we report three KGN-loaded nanoparticles formulations fabricated using nanoprecipitation based on poly(lactic-co-glycolic acid) (PLGA) with varied surface modifications."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s28",
      "source_region_type": "experimental_design",
      "source_locator_text": "EXPERIMENTAL_DESIGN_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "PLGA was selected as a nanoparticle polymer commonly used in delivery of hydrophobic drugs, including KGN."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s29",
      "source_region_type": "experimental_design",
      "source_locator_text": "EXPERIMENTAL_DESIGN_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "Specifically, we developed KGN-loaded PLGA, PLGA–poly(ethylene glycol) (PLGA–PEG), and PLGA–PEG–hyaluronic acid (PLGA–PEG–HA) nanoparticles."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s30",
      "source_region_type": "experimental_design",
      "source_locator_text": "EXPERIMENTAL_DESIGN_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "We sought to vary surface properties from hydrophobic (i.e., PLGA) to hydrophilic (i.e., PLGA–PEG and PLGA–PEG–HA) and surface charge from negative (i.e., PLGA–PEG–HA and PLGA) to positive (i.e., PLGA–PEG)."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s31",
      "source_region_type": "optimization_result",
      "source_locator_text": "OPTIMIZATION_RESULT_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "We noted that PLGA formed the smallest nanoparticles, followed by PLGA–PEG, and finally PLGA–PEG–HA"
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s32",
      "source_region_type": "optimization_result",
      "source_locator_text": "OPTIMIZATION_RESULT_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "Despite a smaller diameter, PLGA nanoparticles had the greatest drug loading of all formulations"
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s33",
      "source_region_type": "optimization_result",
      "source_locator_text": "OPTIMIZATION_RESULT_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "our average particle size was ~ 37% smaller (~ 170 nm vs."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s34",
      "source_region_type": "paragraph",
      "source_locator_text": "PARAGRAPH_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "However, despite the difference in diameter, the EE% of our nanoparticles was similar to this previously reported formulation (62% compared to 67%)."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s35",
      "source_region_type": "paragraph",
      "source_locator_text": "PARAGRAPH_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "Release properties from our PLGA nanoparticles (< 1% release of loaded KGN) differed dramatically from these previously reported KGN-loaded PLGA particles"
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s36",
      "source_region_type": "paragraph",
      "source_locator_text": "PARAGRAPH_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "The PLGA–PEG and PLGA–PEG–HA nanoparticles released greater amounts of KGN than the PLGA nanoparticles"
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s37",
      "source_region_type": "experimental_design",
      "source_locator_text": "EXPERIMENTAL_DESIGN_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "Release from four distinct nanoparticle batches per formulation type are shown indicating variability in KGN release from these particles at the release conditions examined."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "s38",
      "source_region_type": "experimental_design",
      "source_locator_text": "EXPERIMENTAL_DESIGN_BLOCK",
      "supporting_text": "1× PBS at 37 °C"
    },
    {
